Red Bull appears to be the favourites after dominating pre-season testing as Mercedes are likely to struggle early on in the campaign. Lewis Hamilton may not be challenging for race wins from the outset but his contract talks could soon be wrapped up.  The seven-time champion hit out at suggestions he would only sign a deal at Mercedes once has seen how quick the new W14 will be. The remarks were made by ex-British F1 champions Jenson Button and Damon Hill ahead of the opening race. Meanwhile, Max Verstappen and George Russell were told off by F1 journalist Tom Clarkson in yesterday’s drivers’ press conference. The two stars were giggling and chatting seconds before questions began, forcing Clarkson to intervene.